     2| * IVX Owner Authentication Diagnostics service (owner-only).
     3| *
     4| * The watchdog flagged `owner_route_auth_401` — owner-gated routes were falling
     5| * back to /public/chat because the Supabase owner session was invalid/expired.
     6| * This service surfaces the EXACT auth state so the owner can see and fix it,
     7| * instead of a generic error:
     8| *   - current owner token status + expiration
     9| *   - Supabase session status
    10| *   - owner auth middleware result (live probe of the owner-gated backend)
    11| *   - last owner endpoint called + HTTP code + auth failure reason
    12| *   - refresh-token, re-authenticate, and retry actions
    13| *
    14| * When owner auth fails it auto-creates a watchdog incident (POST /api/ivx/incidents,
    15| * source=`auth`) and returns a plain-English fix recommendation. Never logs or
    16| * returns the raw token.
    17| */
    18|import { getDirectApiBaseUrl } from '@/lib/api-base';
